.TH HYPERVISORD 1 "January 2026" "hypervisord 1.0.0" "Hypervisor SDK"
.SH NAME
hypervisord \- VM export daemon with REST API
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hypervisord
[\fB\-\-config\fR \fIFILE\fR]
[\fB\-\-addr\fR \fIADDRESS\fR]
[\fB\-\-log\-level\fR \fILEVEL\fR]
[\fB\-\-version\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hypervisord
is a background daemon that provides a REST API for exporting virtual machines
from VMware vSphere and other hypervisors. It handles job management, concurrent
exports, and progress tracking.
.PP
The daemon connects to vCenter/ESXi using the VMware Go SDK (govmomi) and provides
endpoints for submitting export jobs, querying status, and managing the export queue.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-config " " \fIFILE\fR
Path to configuration file (default: /etc/hypervisord/config.yaml)
.TP
.BR \-\-addr " " \fIADDRESS\fR
HTTP server listen address (default: localhost:8080)
.TP
.BR \-\-log\-level " " \fILEVEL\fR
Set log level: debug, info, warn, error (default: info)
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show version information
.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file uses YAML format and supports the following fields:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
VCenterURL: "https://vcenter.example.com/sdk"
Username: "administrator@vsphere.local"
Password: "secret"
Insecure: true
DaemonAddr: "localhost:8080"
LogLevel: "info"
Download Workers: 4
.fi
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B GOVC_URL
vCenter SDK URL (overrides config file)
.TP
.B GOVC_USERNAME
vCenter username
.TP
.B GOVC_PASSWORD
vCenter password
.TP
.B GOVC_INSECURE
Skip TLS verification (1=yes, 0=no)
.TP
.B DAEMON_ADDR
HTTP server listen address
.TP
.B LOG_LEVEL
Logging level (debug|info|warn|error)
.SH REST API
The daemon exposes the following endpoints:
.TP
.B GET /health
Health check endpoint
.TP
.B GET /status
Daemon status and statistics
.TP
.B POST /jobs/submit
Submit a new export job
.TP
.B POST /jobs/query
Query job status
.TP
.B POST /jobs/cancel
Cancel running jobs
.SH EXAMPLES
Start the daemon with default settings:
.PP
.RS 4
hypervisord
.RE
.PP
Start with custom configuration:
.PP
.RS 4
hypervisord \-\-config /etc/hypervisord/prod.yaml
.RE
.PP
Start with custom listen address:
.PP
.RS 4
hypervisord \-\-addr 0.0.0.0:8080 \-\-log\-level debug
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/hypervisord/config.yaml
Default configuration file
.TP
.I /var/lib/hypervisord/
Working directory for exports
.TP
.I /var/log/hypervisord/
Log directory (when not using systemd journal)
.SH SYSTEMD
The daemon can be managed as a systemd service:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
sudo systemctl start hypervisord
sudo systemctl enable hypervisord
sudo systemctl status hypervisord
sudo journalctl \-u hypervisord \-f
.fi
.RE
